<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-43B08642-B7EC-4DDE-A0E1-D095BEEBEB75" version="2" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-43B08642-B7EC-4DDE-A0E1-D095BEEBEB75" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">05 The process of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M057031-B22"><p class="- topic/p ">This is the functional description of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="FIG_82D50B2845BF4088B137FDAAE0ADB076"><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">Carriage PBA and the connected components 
</p></desc><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-F4699854-3F82-49AE-B2A6-C73AF0DC1A2D-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-F4699854-3F82-49AE-B2A6-C73AF0DC1A2D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> The Carriage PBA has the following functions: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul " id="UL_D9482BEF6E2D44E2924A790AAEBB8F96"><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_68D8D1C42F67487D9AC1B7C04C5C65D3"><p class="- topic/p "> Power supply and distribution 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_AABEC188DE9D464C8FD543C94AB726BF"><p class="- topic/p ">Data path to and from the printheads: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Printhead 3 ... 6: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 3</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH03 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> ... <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 6</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH06 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_26B1956FB6754F99865E661815A9582B"><p class="- topic/p ">Support of sensors and fan: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> M&amp;C unit: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Measurement and control receiver PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05PBA05 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">YMS_CAR_MC_SE</compsignal></comp> and <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Measurement and control LED PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05PBA06 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">YMS_CAR_MC_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Ruler sensor: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Y motion system carriage ruler encoder</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05PBA03 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">YMS_CAR_RUL_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Home sensor: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Y motion system carriage home sensor</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05B1 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">YMS_CAR_HOME_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Fan: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Y motion system carriage cool 1 fan</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 05M2 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">YMS_CAR_COOL1_FAN</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li></ul></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M057031-B23" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Illustration</ph></title><fig outputclass="figure" id="M057031-F24" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp></title><image href="GUID-DFD76864-6A6D-48F0-B8FA-3E47F6ECD8CA-low.png" id="IMAGE_91869182746F450EB51CFDD6A33030C3" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DFD76864-6A6D-48F0-B8FA-3E47F6ECD8CA-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_505294A4D71E4A16A8ABCD2141F931C0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Power supply</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printheads are powered via the Carriage PBA. Power and data is transported via the FPCs ( Flex printhead Cable). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Power for the carriage and the printheads is coming from the main power supplies via the PHD Distribution PBA. The power is then transported via the FFCs (Flex Foil Cable). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To power all onboard functions of the Carriage PBA several power converters are integrated in the PBA. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_E0E512C2F59048C5997ED9E480864C4D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Data path to and from the printheads:</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Carriage PBA is connected to the printer (X350) via the optical link (glass fiber cable). The onboard FPGA (Fixed Programmed Gate Array) is programmed to handle the communication with the printer. The FPGA handles also the communication with the printheads (via connectors X6000 ... X3000). 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_DC9496ABF9C342178979CD6EDAE34B48" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Sensors and fan</title><p class="- topic/p ">The carriage PBA: 
</p><ul id="UL_828F32B620DE45C89E92F001384499A2" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_171D5E726511486897EBFEEE0E80FB26" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Detects the carriage home position by means of the home sensor. 
</p></li><li id="LI_51338549C5BD4E969AECC19E928B76F7" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Detects the carriage relative position and speed by means of the ruler sensor . 
</p></li><li id="LI_4140E5909E9E437087B69B171F1463D1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Communicates with the M&amp;C sensor. 
</p></li><li id="LI_098F6472979B41DF804CB4461A347FE1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Reads the value of the matrix plate NTC sensors. 
</p></li><li id="LI_92EB32FB92F045B9A8CC1428F6650B15" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Controls the “printhead connected” LEDs, the “optical link active” LED, and two user LEDs !! 
</p></li><li id="LI_F3C2AABC54B046B2BBC98BCC01B282BB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Controls the fan which cools the printheads 
</p></li></ul></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EDD196F8-AB74-4704-8B74-A25ED306422F.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
